episodes.title: Why in the Fuck Is My Trailer Pink?
episodes.plot: Julian and Ricky get out of jail and return to Sunnyvale Trailer Park, but when they arrive, they find nothing is as they left it.

episodes.title: A Stable Fucking Environment
episodes.plot: Ricky tries to keep his family together despite not being allowed back in the park, while Julian and Bubbles try to get business going again.

episodes.title: Anointed in Liquor
episodes.plot: Julian hatches a plan to secure a place to live while Ricky and his family struggle with their new life in the barn.

episodes.title: George Green: Industrial Cock Inhaler
episodes.plot: Julian and his crew have a motel auction while Ricky must track down a list full of baby items to keep his family together.

episodes.title: The Motel Can't Live at the Motel
episodes.plot: Ricky brings his grandson home to the motel, but it doesn't go as planned, and Julian implements the first stage in his bid to get Sunnyvale back.

episodes.title: Sweet Liquory Load
episodes.plot: J-Roc struggles with his new role as a father, and Julians plan to get the park back earns Ricky a piece of Leslie's wrath.

episodes.title: Piss
episodes.plot: Mr. Lahey falls off the wagon on the day of Sunnyvale's big appraisal, which Julian, Ricky, and the the crew do their best to ruin.

episodes.title: A Dancer for Money
episodes.plot: Leslie puts Sunnyvale park under lock down, Ricky holds an open house at the motel and Ricky also has an adventure in the woods.

episodes.title: Sam-Squamptches and Heli-Cocksuckers
episodes.plot: Julian gets desperate in his attempt to reclaim Sunnyvale, Ricky finally might get his family back and Mr. Lahey falls further off the wagon.

episodes.title: The Liquor Snurf
episodes.plot: It's morning in Sunnyvale as Julian carries out the final stage of his big reverse psychology plan to get his beloved trailer park back.
